## LAYER 2: TERMS AND CONDITIONS

### 0. Definitions
*   **"The Program"** refers to any copyrightable work licensed under this License.
*   **"Corresponding Source"** means all source code needed to generate, install, run, and modify the Program, including scripts and interface definitions.
*   **"Network Interaction"** means allowing users to interact with the Program remotely through a computer network (e.g., SaaS, Cloud APIs).
*   **"Derived AI Model"** means any machine learning model whose weights, parameters, or logic were generated, fine-tuned, or optimized using the Program as training data or inputs.
*   **"Data Ingestion"** means the automated or manual scraping, downloading, caching, parsing, or processing of the Program's source code, binaries, or outputs for the purpose of training, fine-tuning, or validating machine learning models.
*   **"Installation Information"** includes any cryptographic keys, digital signatures, secure-boot tokens, or hardware unlock methods required to install and execute modified versions of the Program on a specific hardware device.

### 1. Basic Permissions & Copyleft
All rights granted under this License are irrevocable provided the stated conditions are met. You may make, run, and propagate covered works. If you convey (distribute) a modified version of the Program, you must license the entire work, as a whole, under this exact License and provide the complete Corresponding Source to the recipients.

### 2. Protecting Legal Rights (Anti-Circumvention & AI Waiver)
No covered work shall be deemed part of an effective technological measure under any applicable law fulfilling obligations under the WIPO copyright treaty. 
**Contractual Waiver:** By exercising rights under this License, including the Data Ingestion of the Program for machine learning, you explicitly acknowledge that such use is permitted solely by the conditional grant of this License. In consideration for the broad rights granted herein, you agree to waive any "Fair Use" or equivalent statutory defenses regarding the ingestion of this code for the purpose of training proprietary or permissive AI models.

### 3. The Network Trigger (Cloud Interaction)
If you modify the Program and allow users to engage in Network Interaction with it, you must provide those interacting users with a prominent, free, and immediate mechanism to download the complete Corresponding Source of your modified version.

### 4. The Hardware Ally (User Products & Installation)
If you convey an object code work in, or with, a physical "User Product" (consumer or IoT hardware), the Corresponding Source must be accompanied by all Installation Information. You may not use hardware-level locks, firmware checks, or cryptographic signatures to prevent the user from installing and executing their own modified code on the device they own.

### 5. The AI Boundary (Data & Model Reciprocity)
You are granted permission to Data Ingest, process, or utilize the Program for AI training **only under the following condition of strict reciprocity**: If you deploy, sell, or provide network access to a Derived AI Model, you must release the model's full architecture, weights, parameters, and data processing pipeline under this exact License. Utilization of this Program to train models released under permissive, non-copyleft licenses (e.g., MIT, Apache 2.0) or proprietary models without a separate, bilaterally signed commercial agreement is a material breach of this contractual grant.

### 6. Privacy and Anti-Spyware
The Program must not contain mandatory, hidden, or non-opt-in telemetry. Any data collection must be strictly opt-in, fully transparent, and its source code must be included in the Corresponding Source.

### 7. Patents and Defensive Retaliation
Each contributor grants you a non-exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free patent license under their essential patent claims. 
**Defensive Retaliation:** If you initiate litigation (including a cross-claim) alleging that this Program constitutes patent infringement, your patent license and all rights to use this Program are instantly and permanently terminated.

### 8. Termination and 30-Day Cure Period
You may not propagate or modify the Program except as expressly provided under this License. Any attempt otherwise is void and will automatically terminate your rights.
**The Cure:** However, if you cease all violation of this License, your license is reinstated permanently if the copyright holder fails to notify you of the violation within 60 days. Furthermore, your license is reinstated permanently if you receive notice of the violation and cure it prior to 30 days after your receipt of the notice.

### 9. Acceptance and Contractual Nature
You are not required to accept this License to receive a copy. However, nothing other than this License grants you permission to propagate or modify the Program (including Data Ingestion). These actions infringe copyright if you do not accept this License. Therefore, by modifying, propagating, or ingesting the Program for AI training, you indicate your contractual acceptance of this License.

